<TITLE> BNP wants until Jan 25 to file final constitution </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 16 (bdnews24.com)The BNP on Thursday sought six months, until Jan 25, to submit their permanent constitution to the Election Commission, after approval through a party council, a senior leader of the main opposition party said. The deadline for submission is July 25. No political party has submitted their permanent constitutions yet, but Awami League, Jatiya Party and Jamaat-e-Islami have said they were preparing to do so by the deadline. BNP vice-president MK Anwar who led a delegation to a meeting with chief election commissioner ATM Shamsul Huda told reporters that they would submit an application for the extension. The meeting started at the Election Commission Secretariat at around 3:30pm. The BNP delegation included joint secretary Nazrul Islam Khan and office secretary Rizvi Ahmed. Thirty-nine political parties submitted the draft constitution to the EC for registration before the ninth parliamentary elections for provisional registration. According to the Representation of the People Order political parties are to submit their permanent constitutions after approval by national council within six months after parliament convenes. bd
